title: Full Body HIIT Workout | Breakthrough - Day 5
description:
Welcome to your 45 minute full body hiit workout! This workout is going to help you get stronger by using compound exercises for your upper and lower body muscles and we will also boost our metabolism with cardio intervals throughout the workout. This workout is perfect for all fitness levels and you only need a couple sets of dumbbells. 

Grab your January BREAKTHROUGH Program Calendar here: https://shop.royalchange.fit/products/breakthrough-january-2024-workout-stretch-calendar

In today’s workout we will work for 45 seconds and rest for 15 seconds in a circuit of 2 exercises. We will complete each circuit 3 times total before moving on. Each circuit will target your upper and lower body muscles and also aim to get your heart rate up! The training variables we are aiming for this month are strength and improving your conditioning so make sure you’re grabbing weights in the 75%-85% of your max weights range and push yourself to increase the intensity when you are performing a cardio exercise. The cardio exercises can be done on the ground for a low impact modification if you need that but try to push yourself however you perform these exercises. You’ll get the most out of the workout by pushing yourself to your highest intensity in our working periods and breathing in your rests to be able to execute the next set!

The Exercises: 
1.    Squat and side step
2.    Front raises alternating
3.    Jackknives
4.    Mountain Climbers
5.    Plank Hold
6.    Straight Arm pull over and bridge
7.    Lateral Lunges with db switch
8.    DB anchored leg raises
9.    Db Toe taps
10. Glute Bridge
11. Romanian Deadlifts
12. Core flutter and toe touch

channelDescription:
Welcome to your new workout home! I’m your personal trainer and training partner Sydney Cummings Houdyshell and I am a NASM Certified Personal Trainer, Fitness Nutrition Specialist, Women’s Fitness Specialist, and Stretching and Mobility Coach! 
My husband Dustin and I own Royal Change, our fitness company based in Charlotte, NC. I have been an athlete my whole life and I am a West Virginia University Big 12 alum and Track & Field high jump athlete. I still maintain several school and state records for high jump! I have a bachelor's in Child Development studies and after going back to school for a second degree to become a nurse anesthetist, I dropped out during my second year to chase my passion in fitness and personal training! 
When my younger brother passed away in 2017 I knew I had to create something that would leave a legacy so I decided to post my workouts here on YouTube to train people from all over the world with no barriers to anyone! Let’s crush it together!
